## Design Implementation Guidelines

### Layout Structure
- **Hero Section**: Large, impactful with 3D elements and layered backgrounds
- **Services Grid**: Bento-style layout with varying card sizes
- **Testimonials**: Carousel with 3D card effects
- **Product Showcase**: Grid with hover transformations
- **Contact Section**: Interactive form with depth and shadows

### Interactive Elements
- **Buttons**: Neumorphic design with realistic shadows
- **Cards**: 3D hover effects with perspective changes
- **Navigation**: Smooth transitions with depth indicators
- **Forms**: Layered input fields with focus states
- **Modals**: Glassmorphism effects with backdrop blur

### Animation Philosophy
- **Subtle & Purposeful**: Every animation serves a purpose
- **Easing Functions**: Use custom cubic-bezier curves
- **Staggered Animations**: Elements animate in sequence, not simultaneously
- **Hover States**: Realistic feedback with depth changes
- **Loading States**: Sophisticated skeleton screens and progress indicators

## Code Standards
- **Naming**: camelCase (functions/variables), kebab-case (files/folders), PascalCase (components)
- **Comments**: Clear section comments (<!-- HERO SECTION -->)
- **Equality**: Use strict equality (===)
- **Structure**: Modular, organized, lean code
- **Accessibility**: ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, readable contrast
- **CSS Organization**: Logical grouping of styles, custom properties for design tokens

## Image Requirements
- **Format**: ALL images must be .webp
- **Compression**: 80-85% photos, 90-95% graphics
- **Sizes**: Responsive (320px, 640px, 1024px, 1920px)
- **Loading**: Lazy loading on all images
- **Alt text**: Descriptive for accessibility
- **Placement**: Strategic use of images to enhance 3D effects and depth

## Performance Standards
- Minified CSS/JS
